						               													<description>The B-26 has arrived in the European Theater of Operations. It has now joined the B-17, B-24 and the Lancaster over the skies of war torn Europe...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;B-26: The Marauder Strikes! is a solitaire game set onboard a Martin B-26 Marauder medium bomber during World War Two in the European Theater of Operations from July 1943 until the end of the war in May 1945. It is a comprehensive game with several bomber models, mission details and a large selection of targets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game reflects the twin engine B-26 Marauder and situations and events which crews experienced on their missions. If you add the advanced rules you will find &amp;ldquo;B-26&amp;rdquo; to become deep and detailed and you will find yourself in situations where you may have to make decisions that will affect not only the success of your mission, but the fate of your bomber and crew. Historical accuracy has been an important guideline throughout the development of this game, though there are also some &amp;rdquo;what-if,&amp;rdquo; fictional, aspects added.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can begin your campaign flying missions from bases in England then move to the continent later. You will find your station either in England, France, Belgium or the Netherlands, depending on when you fly your campaign. Put together a crew, name your B-26 and fly missions over France, Belgium, the Netherlands, Luxemburg, Germany, Austria and Czechoslovakia!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
